{"title_page": "Enterfear", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Enterfear\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Tech N9ne]]\n| cover        = File:1587035544 tech-n9ne-enterfear.jpg|thumb\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|4|17}}\n| recorded     = 2019\u201320\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length       = {{Duration|h=1|s=54}}\n| label        = [[Strange Music]]\n| producer     = [[Seven (record producer)|Seven]]\n| prev_title   = [[N9na]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = \n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]''\n| rev1score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/culture/music/the-strokes-new-album-rides-a-new-wave-with-flashes-of-synth-fun-20200406-p54hdn.html|title=The Strokes' new album rides a new wave, with flashes of synth fun|last=Lal|first=Kish|date=April 7, 2020|website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Enterfear''''' (stylized in [[all caps]]) is the twenty-second studio album by American rapper [[Tech N9ne]]. It was released on April 17, 2020 via [[Strange Music]]. [[Hip hop production|Production]] was handled mostly by Michael \"[[Seven (record producer)|Seven]]\" Summers. It features [[guest appearance]]s from [[Krizz Kaliko]], King Iso, Landxn Fyre, [[Flatbush Zombies]], Jehry Robinson, Lex Bratcher, Love Mae C, Mackenzie Nicole, Marley Young, Merkules, Nav\u00e9 Monjo and Scru Face Jean.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.55475/title.tech-n9ne-shares-enterfear-album|title=Tech N9ne Shares 'ENTERFEAR' LP|last=Ivey|first=Justin|date=April 16, 2020|website=[[HipHopDX]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe full-length was preceded by two [[extended play]]s: ''EnterFear Level 1'', which was released on November 22, 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.53554/title.tech-n9ne-delivers-enterfear-level-1-ep|title=Tech N9ne Delivers 'EnterFear Level 1' EP|last=Ivey|first=Justin|date=November 21, 2019|website=[[HipHopDX]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref> and ''EnterFear Level 2'', which was released on January 17, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.54166/title.tech-n9ne-releases-enterfear-level-2-ep|title=Tech N9ne Releases 'EnterFear Level 2' EP|last=Ivey|first=Justin|date=January 16, 2020|website=[[HipHopDX]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref> Songs \"Yeah No\", \"Feel So Sad\", \"Angel Baby\", \"On the Outside\" and \"B.I.B.\" were included in the first EP, and the second one was composed of \"Outdone\", \"Leave It On the Flo\", \"Phonk (Leave It On the Flo, Pt. 2)\" and \"Smell Good\".\n\n==Track listing==\nCredits are adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/135898649/credits|title=Try the TIDAL Web Player|last=|first=|date=|website=listen.tidal.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| title1 = Just Die?\n| note1 = Intro 1\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Tech N9ne|Aaron Yates]]|Damon Gomez}}\n| length1 = 2:58\n| title2 = Suckseed (Intro 2)\n| note2 = featuring [[Krizz Kaliko]] and King Iso\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Yates|[[Krizz Kaliko|Samuel Watson]]|Tarrel Gulledge|Gomez}}\n| length2 = 3:09\n| title3 = Outdone\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Yates|[[Seven (record producer)|Michael Summers]]}}\n| length3 = 3:17\n| title4 = Look What I Did\n| note4 = featuring [[Flatbush Zombies]] and Jehry Robinson\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Yates|[[Zombie Juice|Antonio Lewis]]|[[Meechy Darko|Demetry Simms]]|[[Erick Arc Elliott|Erick Elliott]]|Gerald C. Robinson|Summers}}\n| length4 = 4:20\n| title5 = Yeah No!\n| note5 = featuring Mackenzie Nicole\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Yates|Summers}}\n| leng