ums]]\n[[Category:Tech N9ne albums]]\n[[Category:Strange Music albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Seven (record producer)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Enterfear\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Tech N9ne]]\n| cover        = [[File:1587035544 tech-n9ne-enterfear.jpg|thumb]]\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|4|17}}\n| recorded     = 2019\u201320\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length       = {{Duration|h=1|s=54}}\n| label        = [[Strange Music]]\n| producer     = [[Seven (record producer)|Seven]]\n| prev_title   = [[N9na]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = \n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]''\n| rev1score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/culture/music/the-strokes-new-album-rides-a-new-wave-with-flashes-of-synth-fun-20200406-p54hdn.html|title=The Strokes' new album rides a new wave, with flashes of synth fun|last=Lal|first=Kish|date=April 7, 2020|website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Enterfear''''' (stylized in [[all caps]]) is the twenty-second studio album by American rapper [[Tech N9ne]]. It was released on April 17, 2020 via [[Strange Music]]. [[Hip hop production|Production]] was handled mostly by Michael \"[[Seven (record producer)|Seven]]\" Summers. It features [[guest appearance]]s from [[Krizz Kaliko]], King Iso, Landxn Fyre, [[Flatbush Zombies]], Jehry Robinson, Lex Bratcher, Love Mae C, Mackenzie Nicole, Marley Young, Merkules, Nav\u00e9 Monjo and Scru Face Jean.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.55475/title.tech-n9ne-shares-enterfear-album|title=Tech N9ne Shares 'ENTERFEAR' LP|last=Ivey|first=Justin|date=April 16, 2020|website=[[HipHopDX]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe full-length was preceded by